      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BETTOR INTHE DARK (8) looks close to a win after finishing second in both outings so far. Turned in a strong performance last time when she came from this barrier and battled on bravely to just miss out by a head at Wagga. With even luck she looks good enough to put herself in the winners' stall. MRS MAHONEY (2) is a three-year-old filly by Fear The Dragon on debut for Steve Turnbull. Looked above average in winning her latest trial at Bathurst and draws to advantage. Could kick off with a win. JUST KEEP CHIMING (4) is at the track for the first time. By Tall Dark Stranger and hails from the John O'Shea stable. Has strong trial form coming into this, winning her latest hitout at Bathurst. Anticipating a bright start to her career. Betting Line filly WINDY HILL ABBEY (3) is another on debut for the Steve Turnbull yard. Has been trialling nicely and draws well so keep safe.",
